libdice - need to roll 100d61? no problem.

Take a look at example.c to see it in action.

Here's a short rundown:

init_dice() - Starts number generator and other setup.
finish_dice() - Cleanup any *FILEs and malloc.

dice_parse() - Digest dice-roll string.
  On failure, dice_error is set.
  Return value, 1 on success and 0 on failure.

dice_perror() - Prints given string, then the dice error.
dice_strerror() - Given dice_error, return error string.
